Delicious
Fun stop for foot traffic on Gilbert Road. Simple menu for grab and go food.  The prickly pear ice cream is a fun thing to get, and it’s pretty good too.

Was taken here the other night. The burritos are a good size. The chicken burrito is better than the pork in my opinion. The pork was what seemed to be BBQ pork. The elote was good too but not wow. Too full to get to the soft serve but will come back for the prickly pear.
My husband and I experienced the prickly pear cone dipped in lime and it was excellent. Can't tell you what it tasted like for comparison purposes, but it was worth the trip from Wisconsin!
Yum
Different type of burrito bbq with a Mexican twist very tasty good customer service just wanted more to choose from but all around worth a try

We got a Topo Burrito and 2 cones. The staff was great! They offered to let us get our cones after we were done with our burritos and I thought that was very nice. Chicken Burrito was delicious - it had a sweetish, but subtley spices quick. …
Great burritos, large portions, quick service, fabulous experience

Prickly pear swirled with vanilla dipped in chocolate is my go to. Crave it all summer. Friendly & fast service. They take cards only, no cash. My fam loves hanging out in the hammocks with our cones. Great grassy area to eat at.

A cute area and building. Friendly staff. simple menu with incredible flavor. I definitely recommend the the prickly pear soft serve with the lime dip. Picnic tables to the left of the building is a nice area to hang out.
Simple and delicious!!!
If your looking for a simple menu but great food, this is the place to be! Quick easy ordering, but great burritos amd icecream. Our kids loved the prickly pear flavored icecream.
Duuuuude. Supreme
Awesome unique burritos full of flavor and high quality ingredients
Prickly pear ice cream is amazing
Super tasty! 😊
Great soft ice cream at a good price.
The prickly pear froyo is so good!

We road our bikes to downtown Gilbert just for fun. Decided to try Topo. Had a great burrito like I would have created at home. Not ridiculously huge or unwieldy but definitely not your slap-n-serve fast food variety either. Coupled with a cold beer and outdoor dining. Nice! I'll be back.
Soft serve is great . 6yo approved and recommends getting the twist Chicken topo burrito flavor is fantastic, but i wish it was bigger for the price compared to chipotle being its $7.

Friendly service and some of the best elote ever, I always order two when I go ❤

Please tell the server to not forget the fritos as the what really makes the burritos. Disappointed coming home and 3/4 did not have them. Also did burritos get smaller as last year I remember being bigger?
Soft severe is good, but the burrito keeps me coming back.. so delicious, smoked pork and elote... Definitely worth trip from mesa
I need everyone to know how awesome the burritos are here. And the ice cream. You NEED to try it. But seriously, best burrito I’ve ever had.

The BEST Burritos! Simple and so good with pork from Joe's Real bbq. Love that it's open late.

Been going to Joe's since I was a kid and finally tonight my girlfriend and I decided to try Topo's and I'll just say it was absolutly amazing! So good!! Limited menu but everything we tried was excellent! My fav was the Prickly Pear ice cream cone dipped in Lime!

ice cream is good

Amazing ice cream and fun energetic staff

This is perfect burrito sold at the perfect location so you can people watch, see water tower lit up with Christmas colors. And drink a real cane sugar Coke. We did this several times.

I love this place. Simple menu and amazing food! They use Joe's Real BBQ pork and it tastes AMAZING! Very tasty drink selection. Ice cream is the best!! Right nextdoor to Joe's BBQ
Burrito was the bomb and the icecream was fire.
Okay. Meat was smoky. Made me feel like an idiot because I didn't know the routine.  I hadn't been there before. Cute outdoor set up
great soft serve

Ice cream is good.
Really enjoyed this place. Had tried the soft serve before & loved it. Tried the burrito tonight and also really liked it. I'm not blown away, but would definitely eat it again.
We just stopped by for the prickly pear soft serve cone. It was delicious.
Their Topo Loco burritos are a potheads dream. Sweet, salty, savory and spicy. Big portions, but waiting in line can be tough in the heat of the sun. Dipped cones are good, but not life changing.

Definitely a new downtown staple! Something to show the tourists and take a photo in front of! Got the prickly pear soft serve dipped in lime- the ice cream was good (tried the twist and it was even better!) I wasn't blown away by the lime …

The Topo Loco is spicy and incredible! The sweetness of the elote balances it out perfectly. Will definitely be coming back!

Small street side kiosk that has fantastic burritos and prickly pear ice cream. Get the vanilla mixed with prickly pear flavor and dip it in chocolate. You won't regret it. Sometimes has a line, but it moves very quickly.
Party of the Joe's BBQ, excellent food. And the prickly ice cream.
Such a cool addition to Gilbert!  I'm seriously hooked on the prickly pear twist cones... can't walk into town without stopping for one.  And the street corn is fab!

Topo Arizona. Good place. Small menu, but each item is great. I got the Topo Loco burrito with chicken. The hot sauce is hot and has great flavor. I got extra hot sauce on the side because I love the burn.

Their burrito is one solid burrito! It had the perfect texture and weight to it. I’m a fan of Jalapeño Bucks up north, but this trumps their burritos any day. I was a little concerned at how small the menu was, but they definitely opted to specialize. Great smoky flavor. All around a 10/10 burrito. 👌💪🙌👍
Small portion of corn for the price but it was good. The burrito was expensive but good.

Love it! Awesome burritos, Elote and Ice cream!
Family loved the Prickly Pear Ice Cream!

Simple cool spot! Whether you want to have some elote or some great ice cream this place is great. Cool spot to hang out with a big group.

Great ice cream!

Very simple menu and good tasting food.  The spot is off the sidewalk and the line to order can get crowded next to Gilbert Rd, keep an eye on the kids!  The eating area is great and the ice cream was delicious.

Simple menu.  So far I’ve only had the ice cream.  Vanilla dipped in chocolate.  Prickly Pear is my favorite, but when you dip it in Lime dip it will change your point of view of what ever you thought was your favorite ice cream... Trust …

I love this little food stand and the environment around it. It’s a perfect place to stop for a quick bite or celebrate the end of a week. The outdoor garden area offers some relaxing entertainment as well.

🌯🍦🐶Check this place out! Love the idea and don't let the line scare you as it moves very quickly. You have burritos, street corn, and soft serve with some Mexican Coke as a kicker if you like. There's some nice but limited seating and don't forget to view the mural on the wall🖼️ PS it's super dog friendly;)
Definitely worth the wait in line!
Delicious prickly pear soft serve and fast service. Right in the heart of downtown Gilbert with family friendly area to sit and relax.

Dont let the line scare you, we got our food real quick after we ordered. Definitely recommend the soft serve prickly pear dipped in lime. Burritos are good! Bring water, they dont have any. otherwise you can buy a $3 soda bottle or go next door to joes bbq for a water cup (when i tried joes line was too long).

Ordered the Topo Loco with pork, and a Prickly Pear ice cream cone. Both were fantastic,  the only downside is the line but thats understandable as to it being a new joint. Definitely am going back when i get a chance.

Ordered the burrito...AMAZING!!  I WILL be back..great job guys. Food came quick and very fresh ingredients!

Vibes of yesteryear with the taste of today. The Elotes are fresh and the Topo Loco is on point!
